<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="412" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1638,2023]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="412" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1710,1735]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Length of forewing is 
<quantity box="[599,702,1710,1735]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" unit="mm" value="11.5">11.5 mm</quantity>
in male. The species is similar externally only to 
<taxonomicName pageId="10" pageNumber="411" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="pellucida">
Javanese 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">N. pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its red subterminal forewing area (in all other red patterned species the subterminal area is white with three large red spots) and the dark greyish hindwings, but differs by the narrower forewings, the broader transverse lines, the larger medial spot, and the larger discal spots. The male genitalia differ clearly from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[151,290,1854,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Chionaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis box="[151,290,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">N. pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the narrower apical lobes of the juxta, the less developed medial costal angle, the much broader distal section of the costa, the much larger, lobe-like apical process of the costa, the larger ventral-apical costal process, the broader sacculus with the shorter subapical process, the slightly larger carinal plate of the aedeagus, the smaller distal diverticulum of the vesica having the cluster of larger spines, the absence of a subbasal diverticulum, and the medial diverticulum narrower and directed basally. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1212,1435,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wolfgangspeideli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1212,1435,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">N. wolfgangspeideli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,241,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,241,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from those of it relatives 
<taxonomicName box="[600,721,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Chionaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effracta">
<emphasis box="[600,721,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">N. effracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Kirti, Joshi &amp; N. Singh" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[775,974,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoeffracta">
<emphasis box="[775,974,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">N. pseudoeffracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the broader distal section of the costa, the broader ventral-apical costal process, the smaller, broadly trigonal ampulla, the broader subapical saccular process, the smaller aedeagus, the significantly narrower vesica, the absence of a subbasal diverticulum, and the significantly smaller medial and distal diverticula.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" box="[199,470,295,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="412">The female is unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
